Yakov Faitelson Sells 56,085 Shares of Varonis Systems, Inc. (VRNS) Stock

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 

Varonis Systems, Inc. (NASDAQ:VRNS) CEO Yakov Faitelson sold 56,085 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction that occurred on Friday, June 23rd. The stock was sold at an average price of $37.04, for a total transaction of $2,077,388.40. Following the completion of the sale, the chief executive officer now directly owns 397,083 shares of the company’s stock, valued at approximately $14,707,954.32. The sale was disclosed in a filing with the SEC, which is accessible through the SEC website. 
Yakov Faitelson also recently made the following trade(s): 





On Monday, July 10th, Yakov Faitelson sold 7,000 shares of Varonis Systems stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $38.00, for a total transaction of $266,000.00. 
On Friday, May 26th, Yakov Faitelson sold 915 shares of Varonis Systems stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $37.00, for a total transaction of $33,855.00. 
On Thursday, May 4th, Yakov Faitelson sold 8,657 shares of Varonis Systems stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $32.01, for a total transaction of $277,110.57. 
On Tuesday, May 2nd, Yakov Faitelson sold 50,818 shares of Varonis Systems stock. The stock was sold at an average price of $32.03, for a total transaction of $1,627,700.54. 
On Monday, May 1st, Yakov Faitelson sold 33,320 shares of Varonis Systems stock. The shares were sold at an average price of $32.00, for a total transaction of $1,066,240.00. 
On Wednesday, May 3rd, Yakov Faitelson sold 91,385 shares of Varonis Systems stock. The shares were sold at an average price of $32.02, for a total transaction of $2,926,147.70. 
On Monday, April 3rd, Yakov Faitelson sold 8,000 shares of Varonis Systems stock. The shares were sold at an average price of $32.02, for a total transaction of $256,160.00. 
On Monday, March 27th, Yakov Faitelson sold 49,273 shares of Varonis Systems stock. The shares were sold at an average price of $31.00, for a total transaction of $1,527,463.00. 

Varonis Systems, Inc. (VRNS) traded down 0.13% on Friday, reaching $38.50. The company had a trading volume of 165,093 shares. The company’s 50 day moving average price is $37.03 and its 200-day moving average price is $32.19. Varonis Systems, Inc. has a 12 month low of $23.71 and a 12 month high of $39.30. The company’s market capitalization is $1.05 billion. 


 Get Varonis Systems Inc. alerts:



Varonis Systems (NASDAQ:VRNS) last announced its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, May 4th. The technology company reported ($0.23) earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of ($0.30) by $0.07. The company had revenue of $40.40 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $37.45 million. Varonis Systems had a negative return on equity of 23.33% and a negative net margin of 10.46%. The company’s revenue for the quarter was up 32.5% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the prior year, the company earned ($0.29) earnings per share. 
